The paper deals with abnormal event detection in video, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel framework that requires no training sequences, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also compares its method with several state-of-the-art methods, which indicates that it may belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM) or cryptography and security (cs.CR).
